Package api

Class AbstractElement

java.lang.Object
api.AbstractElement
All Implemented Interfaces:
Drawable
Direct Known Subclasses:
SimpleElement
public abstract class AbstractElement extends Object implements Drawable
Implementation of the Drawable interface associates a drawable object with a Renderer to use for drawing. In addition, this class specifies some features useful for elements in a 2d video game.

Every element has an "exact" position represented by an (x, y) pair of floating-point values. This position is the upper-left corner of a bounding rectangle whose width and height are additional attributes. Other attributes include a frame counter and a flag that allows an application to "mark" an object for subsequent deletion. A key operation is the update method, which an application would normally call each frame. At a minimum the update method should increment the frame count, but more generally, subclasses would override the method to implement features such as movement.
